-- Merrill, Goldman, Morgan fall after Lehman
-- 
-- Wed Sep 10, 2008 8:36am EDT
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2008/09/10/us-markets-stocks-beforethebell-banks-idUSN1039890720080910

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of top U.S. investment banks fell on Wednesday after Lehman Brothers posted a steeper-than-expected quarterly loss and slashed its annual dividend.  

 In pre-market trading on the New York Stock Exchange, shares of Merrill Lynch were down 4 percent at $23.80; those of Goldman Sachs down 2 percent at $158.55 and those of Morgan Stanley were down 1.6 percent at  $39.75. (Reporting by  Richard Leong ; Editing by  James Dalgleish )